hands_on_practices.introduction:
Bessel functions of the second kind, $Y_{
u}(x)$, often seem abstract. This first exercise grounds these functions in familiar territory by connecting them to elementary trigonometry. By working through the derivation for the special case of order $
u = 1/2$, you will see how the formal definition of $Y_{
u}(x)$ can yield a simple, concrete function, providing valuable intuition for the nature of these solutions. [@problem_id:2127662]
